************** G E N E R A L   I N F O R M A T I O N ************ 7525 1451
                                                                  7525 1451
This evaluated data file is based primarily on the nuclear model  7525 1451
code Talys [kon07], version 1.0 and on existing resonance         7525 1451
parameter tables. It is part of a large collection of isotopic    7525 1451
evaluations, all created by running Talys with default input      7525 1451
parameters. This means that the data in this evaluation have not  7525 1451
been tested in detail against individual experimental data for    7525 1451
this isotope, but is only as good as the global quality of Talys  7525 1451
at the present moment. The mutual quality of all individual       7525 1451
evaluations is thus relatively consistent. The same set of        7525 1451
nuclear models is used and, equally important, the same ENDF-6    7525 1451
formatting procedures for each isotope. The resulting data file   7525 1451
provides a complete representation of nuclear data needed for     7525 1451
transport, damage, heating, radioactivity, and shielding          7525 1451
applications over the incident neutron energy range from 1.0E-11  7525 1451
to 20 MeV. A complete set of covariance data is included.         7525 1451
                                                                  7525 1451
For the resonance range, Talys can not yet be used. Hence, for    7525 1451
low energies we have adopted the best possible resonance data     7525 1451
from an existing library.                                         7525 1451
                                                                  7525 1451
All transport data for neutrons, other particles, photons and     7525 1451
residual nuclides are filed using a combination of MF1,2,3,4      7525 1451
and MF6. This includes cross sections, angular distributions,     7525 1451
double-differential spectra, discrete and continuum photon        7525 1451
production cross sections, and residual production (activation)   7525 1451
cross sections. Moreover, isomeric production data are stored in  7525 1451
MF8 and MF10. This evaluation can thus be used as both transport  7525 1451
and activation library. The data file has been created            7525 1451
automatically using the ENDF format generator endl2endf at        7525 1451
Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory.                           7525 1451
